<body>
  <h1>🎨 My Body Builders: 3D Bioprinting Fun for Kids (Ages 3–6)</h1>

  <div class="week">
    <h2>Week 1: 🧠 Meet Your Body!</h2>
    <p>Your body has many amazing parts like your heart, brain, and bones. They help you think, move, and feel. Today, we’ll learn where they go!</p>
    <div class="activity">
      🎨 Activity: Color the body outline and stick the heart, brain, and tummy where they belong!
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="week">
    <h2>Week 2: 🔬 What Are Cells?</h2>
    <p>Your body is made of tiny, tiny pieces called cells. They are too small to see, but they build everything in your body!</p>
    <div class="activity">
      🔵 Activity: Make cells out of playdough and create a tissue by putting many together.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="week">
    <h2>Week 3: 🖨️ What Is a 3D Printer?</h2>
    <p>A 3D printer makes shapes by adding layers. It can print toys, tools, and even things for your body!</p>
    <div class="activity">
      🧱 Activity: Use cookie cutters or building blocks to make shapes in layers.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="week">
    <h2>Week 4: 🏥 Fixing Bodies with Bioprinters</h2>
    <p>Bioprinters help doctors fix skin, bones, and more by making new parts from living cells.</p>
    <div class="activity">
      🩹 Activity: Make your own pretend bandage and help your stuffed toy friend feel better!
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="week">
    <h2>Week 5: 🧪 My Future Lab!</h2>
    <p>You can be a scientist who helps people. Dream big, build things, and be kind!</p>
    <div class="activity">
      🧤 Activity: Draw your own science lab and decorate a pretend lab coat!
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="certificate">
    <h2>🏆 Certificate of Completion</h2>
